Documentation

type family Select (s :: ASTSelector) (ast :: a) = (v :: Type) Source #

Used to select a field type for a given AST.

Conventions for usage: If a selection is likely to be one of the principal newtypes (Expr, Pattern, etc), it should not be wrapped in ASTLocate, as this increases friction and creates redundant Located wrappers. This means that implementations should manually wrap in Locate if not using one of the principal newtypes

class RUnlocate (ast1 :: ast) where Source #

The idea of this class is to provide a way to work under both located and unlocated ASTs We define functions which are polymorphic over the location strategy used in the AST For example, rUnlocate provides a way to extract the unlocated value from an AST node, regardless of whether the AST is located or unlocated
